title: For Sale:  Advanced CWP Course
location: Horry and surrounding counties, Myrtle Beach, South Carolina
postcontent:
The Advanced Concealed Weapons course is an 8 hour class implementing a defensive gun handling course and the ability to develop skills necessary to be successful in a deadly encounter. We will cover multiple scenarios that could occur in your everyday life and how to appropriately respond (an intruder in your home, carjacking in a parking lot, purse snatching, assaults, targets advancing on you, moving targets, etc). These scenarios will be in a live fire environment where you will be improving your skills and techniques involved in drawing your concealed weapon and engaging a target. This is a vital aspect of carrying concealed that is rarely addressed, and without practice or knowing how to respond, the delay in decision making can mean the difference between success or failure. You will be enhancing your skills in drawing from concealment, point shooting, tactical positioning, firing while moving, firing from a vehicle, flash sight picture, shooting from cover, and moving after shooting. 
The purpose of this class is to build your skills as a Concealed Weapons permit holder and practicing the skills needed to use your gun in a defensive confrontation. Additionally, we will cover aspects of carrying concealed that are not discussed in the basic CWP class such as; identifying potentially dangerous persons/situations, awareness, how to react in adverse situations, and practical exercises related to everyday situations. Being prepared and ready for a confrontation is the first step to winning. Through practical experience on the range, skill building, and being prepared you will lessen the probability of becoming the target of criminals. 
A large portion of the course will be on the range. At least 200-300 rounds will be fired. You are encouraged to bring the firearm you carry to the class along with your concealed carry holster. This will allow you to make better decisions on how to carry your handgun based on your physical size and method of carry. If you desire to use one of our guns to get a feel for a different style we will have the appropriate ammunition for the gun (price varies per caliber).
Cost- $100

Selling my long-range "Hammer of God". 
Would be willing to sell just the gun, or just the optic. Email me to discuss. 
I bought this new less than 2 years ago, put a TON of work and money into it. 
It started life as a Rem 700 Sendero in 300 WM. 
I've got a Leupold MK4 6.5-20 Illum reticle mounted to it with a Nightforce 20MOA canted base and Nightforce lightweight rings. Nothing cheap, all high-end.
No expense was spared on this and it shoots .5MOA all day long out to over a thousand with 210 Berger VLD's, so long as the shooter holds his wind correctly.

It's got a JP enterprises custom muzzle brake blended into the barrel with a new match crown. Kicks a bit less than a .308 and you can spot your hits. 
The bolt itself and the large custom bolt handle have been fluted and painted to match by Twisted Barrel out of Wyoming. I spent a ton of money on these cosmetic features, they look awesome. Probably hard to tell from the iPhone pictures. It may look dirty or blurry, but that's just the camera. The gun is in excellent condition, no scratches or scrapes. Really. It's pristine.

The stock and Detachable Mag are H-S precision; it's their top of the line stock. Spent close to a thousand for these 2 items alone! 
Timney 2lb trigger along with the stock pro-mark trigger are included. 
The gun was $1600 new, and with all the accessories, custom machining and optic, I've got easily $5K into this. Not including dies, brass and ammo. 

I have just shy of 500 rounds through this and have a darn good load developed that shoots at long distance very well. 

Really, it's a shooter and doesn't need a thing! Only selling because I've got the long-range bug and bought a .338 Lapua.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Vepr 12-Russian 12 guage AK shotgun!!
postcontent:
The Vepr 12 from the Molot manufactory in Russia is the finest semi-automatic combat shotgun in existence. This is the shotgun that every Saiga 12 WANTS to be but cannot. Only 1000 have been shipped into the country as of yet--but being an AK at heart, most aftermarket accessories are still interchangeable.

The Vepr 12 was designed with an auto gas regulator (unlike its little brother, the Saiga) meaning that you can reliably feed ANY 2 3/4 or 3 inch shells you can find without manual adjustment from birdshot to buckshot, low to high brass. Unlike the Saiga, the Vepr 12 was based on the RPK instead of the standard AK, which means that the receiver is thicker, has a hinged dust cover, and has a polymer rail on top. Also included in the design is an auto-bolt hold open and a magwell which allows for AR-15 style magazine changes instead of rock and lock.

Instead of explaining every new intricacy, watch this great video by the Military Arms Channel on youtube to get an idea of all of its features.
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fMfzN5LZc3o

I have added a Magpul rail to the lower handguard, as well as a vertical foregrip. Additionally, I have replaced the standard wooden stock with a sturdy clubfoot. The Vepr would come with two 10 round SGM magazines and 1 original Russian 5 round.

I've sent roughly 150 shells down the tube and I am QUITE fond of my deadly new toy. Please dont hesitate to send any questions that you may have--im sure that I didnt answer every question you might have in this ad. Im a gun enthusiast though and I am constantly buying/selling/trading so show me what you have in trade. Thanks for looking!

One lightly used COMPLETE NFA poly lower- If you are looking at these, it's important to note that usually out of the box, they will have a hard time with military primers- you'll get light strikes. This is the same stuff they sell to the competitive sharp-shooters in the military (http://www.shootingtimes.com/2011/01/04/ammunition_bh_080305/).  I received this as part of a trade, and I really can not do it justice since I am more of a bulk shooter.

$60/box - FTF from Park Meadows down to Larkspur
